# Next.js 15 + Vercel Development Standards

**Context**: Building modern web applications with Next.js 15+ (App Router) deployed on Vercel.

## Core Principles

1. **App Router Only** - Never use Pages Router for new projects
2. **Server Components by Default** - Only use Client Components when necessary
3. **TypeScript Strict** - Full type safety, no `any` types
4. **Performance First** - Every decision impacts Core Web Vitals
5. **Static When Possible** - Maximize SSG/ISR to minimize costs
6. **SEO Native** - Metadata and structure built-in from start
7. **Accessibility Required** - WCAG AA compliance non-negotiable

## Project Structure

### Recommended Directory Layout

```
app/
├── (marketing)/           # Route group for public pages
│   ├── page.tsx           # Homepage (/)
│   ├── about/             # About page
│   ├── pricing/           # Pricing page
│   └── layout.tsx         # Marketing layout
├── (app)/                 # Route group for authenticated app
│   ├── dashboard/         # Dashboard pages
│   ├── settings/          # Settings pages
│   └── layout.tsx         # App layout with auth
├── api/                   # API routes (use sparingly)
│   └── [...]/route.ts     # API endpoints
├── layout.tsx             # Root layout
├── globals.css            # Global styles
├── not-found.tsx          # Custom 404
├── error.tsx              # Error boundary
├── loading.tsx            # Loading UI
└── sitemap.ts             # Dynamic sitemap

components/
├── ui/                    # Base UI components (shadcn/ui)
├── layout/                # Layout components (Header, Footer)
├── features/              # Feature-specific components
└── shared/                # Shared components

lib/
├── utils.ts               # Utility functions
├── db.ts                  # Database client
├── api.ts                 # API client
└── validations.ts         # Zod schemas

public/
├── images/                # Static images
├── fonts/                 # Static fonts (prefer next/font)
